>QUESTION:
>Has anyone attempted this?  Does Fox absolutely require a R/W medium as far as 
>the startup location is concerned?  Is this controllable by the config.fp?
>
Try the same solution that people that create network apps use.  create a 
subdirectory for all the temp files and user definitions that fox needs on the 
local hard drive.  The amount of info here is small, so it should not be a 
problem.  Do the following:
1) In the autoexec.bat:  SET FOXPROWCFG=C:\dirpath\CONFIG.FPW
     Note the "w" stuff implies windows
2) Create a config.fpw, some of the stuff in ours includes:
  RESOURCE=c:\path\IQSUSER.DBF
  OVERLAY=C:\path\OVERWRITE
  EDITWORK=C:\patht\
  SORTWORK=C:\path\
  PROGWORK=C:\path\
  TMPFILES=C:\path\
  _FOXDOC=""
  _FOXGRAPH=""
  _GENGRAPH=""
  MOUSE=5
  bucket=3
  EMS=ON
  MVCOUNT=1536
  READBORDER=ON
  KEYCOMP = WINDOWS
  CATMAN=OFF
  SET PATH=%PATH%;additional paths;
 
Don't worry if you don't know what half the stuff above is, most of them are 
defaults anyway.  This should get you going.  Good luck!!


