In article <gamez.357.2F26DEFA@sec-521.jpl.nasa.gov>, gamez@sec-521.jpl.nasa.gov (Enrique Gamez) says:
>Has anyone attempted this?  Does Fox absolutely require a R/W medium as far as 
>the startup location is concerned?  Is this controllable by the config.fp?
>
>TIA - Enrique.

FP doesn't necessary requires W-access to the home directory - you can test it by
placing your executable on read-only network drive.  However, FP creates multiple
temporary files at the location specified by the "TMPFILES" variable in the
CONFIG.FPW file. 
1)Put a line in your CONFIG.FPW: 
TMPFILES = c:\
2)Make sure that CONFIG.FPW is in the path, so it could be found by FP at startup
3)Have a nice day!

-MM

